/var/run/postgresql:5432:privatenet:*:*

# We will set a PGPASSFILE environment variable with the location to this file
# The postgresql-setup.sh script in the cardano-db-sync project looks up this file based on the PGPASSFILE env. variable

# More information about the pgpass file - https://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/libpq-pgpass.html

# What do the tokens mean above
# Host:Port:Database_Name:User:Password
# The host can also be a path to the default socket directory
# 5432 is the default PostgreSQL listening port
# privatenet is the name of our database.  It can be modified as desired.
# The user and password are not specified as we are using a Linux system account mapped to a PostgreSQL superuser role

